## Comprehensive Pagination Testing Strategy

### Core Test Scenarios

**Boundary Testing**: Verify first page, last page, and empty result sets. Test page sizes from 1 to maximum allowed values, ensuring proper handling when results don't divide evenly.

**Data Consistency**: Validate that total count matches sum of all pages, no duplicates appear across pages, and sorting remains stable throughout pagination. Cross-reference items to ensure no data loss.

**Error Handling**: Test invalid inputs including negative page numbers, zero page sizes, oversized requests beyond limits, and malformed parameters to ensure graceful degradation.

**Concurrent Testing**: Implement parallel pagination requests to detect race conditions, data inconsistencies under load, and ensure cursor/offset accuracy when multiple clients paginate simultaneously.

### Implementation Example

```javascript
// Comprehensive test suite
describe('API Pagination', () => {
  const pageSizes = [1, 10, 50, 100, 1000];

  test.each(pageSizes)('pagination consistency for size %d', async (size) => {
    const allItems = [];
    let page = 1;
    let hasMore = true;

    // Fetch all pages
    while (hasMore) {
      const response = await api.get('/items', {
        params: { page, size }
      });

      expect(response.data.items).toHaveLength(Math.min(size, response.data.remaining));
      allItems.push(...response.data.items);
      hasMore = response.data.hasMore;
      page++;
    }

    // Validate no duplicates
    const uniqueItems = new Set(allItems.map(item => item.id));
    expect(uniqueItems.size).toBe(allItems.length);

    // Verify total count
    const totalCount = await api.get('/items/count');
    expect(totalCount.data.count).toBe(allItems.length);
  });

  test('concurrent pagination safety', async () => {
    const concurrentRequests = Array(10).fill().map(() => 
      api.get('/items', { params: { page: 1, size: 50 } })
    );

    const responses = await Promise.all(concurrentRequests);
    const firstResponse = responses[0].data.items;

    // All concurrent requests should return identical first page
    responses.forEach(response => {
      expect(response.data.items).toEqual(firstResponse);
    });
  });

  test('edge cases', async () => {
    // Test invalid inputs
    await expect(api.get('/items', { params: { page: -1 } }))
      .rejects.toThrow('Invalid page number');

    await expect(api.get('/items', { params: { size: 0 } }))
      .rejects.toThrow('Invalid page size');

    // Test empty results
    const emptyResponse = await api.get('/items', {
      params: { filter: 'nonexistent' }
    });
    expect(emptyResponse.data.items).toHaveLength(0);
    expect(emptyResponse.data.totalCount).toBe(0);
  });
});
```

